AB  - The significance of the water disasters caused by the climate change is determined by two main factors. The first one depends both on the amount of rainfalls and on the landscape of the ground. The second factor is related to the world economic crisis and the lack of enough investments in new hydraulic structures as well as in preventive reconstruction and modernization of the existing ones.
   There are two groups of problems which may bring about the irrigation dams to an emergency state. These problems are considered with the help of two specific examples of irrigation dams. The first group represents the landslide processes in the downstream batter of the dam. They grow up and increase the risk of breaking the dam. The second group of problems is related to the disruption of the outlet integrity.
   The analysis of the reasons leads to recommendations for efficient overcoming of emergency conditions, caused by weather impacts and lack of funding.
