FX  - We thank Gisborne Council for access to their cross section surveys and other key time-series data; in particular, Brian Currie and Ian Hughes for their survey work in the catchment and Greg Hall for his provision of environmental data. Ernslaw One LTD (Bill Wheeler), has generously provided us with site access and use of their LiDAR database; Hannah Mountfort provided digitization and statistical summaries of the Mangarere fan (Fig. 8) as well as the lower Waiapu (Fig. 12). Edith Bretherton summarized cross section data for the Tapuaeroa and major tributaries. Work by Michelle Reeve inspired the summary of the lhungia gully system. Field assistance by Brendan Hall, Dave Wackrow, Yasmin Walley, Thomas Parkner, and Brett Eaton is gratefully acknowledged, as is support from the GEOG 745 field class at the University of Auckland. We thank Manu Caddie, colleagues from the He Oranga Trust (Tui Warmenhoven and Pia Pohatu), and land owners and community members who have provided access, logistical support, and discussion to help us unravel some of the 30-year history of this catchment. A research development grant from the University of Auckland's Research Office (Tunnicliffe, 3706523) provided key financial support for this work.
