TI  - Influence of Lead (Pb) on the Antioxidation System of Dishlia
T2  - ADVANCES IN ENVIRONMENTAL ENGINEERING
LA  - English
CP  - Global Conference on Civil, Structural and Environmental Engineering / 3rd International Symp on Multi-field Coupling Theory of Rock and Soil Media and its Applications
KW  - Dishlia
KW  - Lead
KW  - Stress
AB  - The method of culturing in nutrient solution is used to research the influence of lead on the antioxidation system of dishlia. Results show that lead treatment can change the content of chlorophyll, MDA, SOD, POD and CAT of dishlia. As the time of treatment goes by, their contents all exhibit a rise-fall pattern of change. Compared with the control plant, lead treatment is inhibitory at the initial stage of the experiment, but promotes growth at a later stage.
   Heavy metal in soil is characterized by stable existence, easy accumulation and difficult in removal. Phytoremediation, with its distinctive low cost, high efficiency and safety assurance, has become an emerging technology in the area of remediating heavy metal pollution in the soil. Dishlia, belonging to Araceae and Alocasia, is a perennial herbal crop. Known for its economy and high pharmaceutical value, dishlia is widely used in medicine and civil industries. Recent years have witnessed reports of its application in treating urban sewage([1]). Using dishlia as the test sample, this research studies the influence of metal lead on the antioxidation system of dishlia and explores the tolerance mechanism of the plant against heavy metal lead.
