TI  - Lime mud washing models, simulators and supervisory control
T2  - 2001 INTERNATIONAL CHEMICAL RECOVERY CONFERENCE: CHANGING RECOVERY TECHNOLOGY TO MEET THE CHALLENGES OF THE PULP AND PAPER INDUSTRY
LA  - English
CP  - International Chemical Recovery Conference
AB  - The competitive situation necessitates operation of the kiln and caustic area with one operator, at the same time reducing white liquor variability. Montoring and acting on the lime mud washing controls normally constitutes more than 50% of the recaust and kiln operator's chores. We needed a lime mud washing supervisory control system that would provide mud filter cake with washable soda content in an acceptable range; provide even strength weak wash, high process reliability and reduce the monitoring and control action requirements to a minimum.
   We developed models for different mud washing technologies and verified them to accurately predict the washable soda content of the mud filter cake. A method for benchmarking efficiency of different brands of lime mud precoat filters and pressure disc filters evolved in the process. The method is used on-line to determine the current washing efficiency of an operating filter.
   The model based supervisory control systems are is used to control mudflows, dilution flows, mud densities, rake torques and tank levels. In off-line applications the model based simulators are used for operator training and new causticiaing plant design. In on-line open loop applications the models are used to provide process overview. The on-line open loop applications are used to pinpoint field instruments in need of calibration.
