TI  - Using multiple-criteria decision-making techniques for eco-environmental vulnerability assessment: a case study on the Chi-Jia-Wan Stream watershed, Taiwan
T2  - ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING AND ASSESSMENT
LA  - English
KW  - Eco-environmental vulnerability
KW  - Analytical Hierarchy Process (AHP)
KW  - Preference Ranking Organization METHod for Enrichment Evaluations (PROMETHEE)
KW  - INDUCED LANDSLIDE HAZARD
KW  - CATASTROPHIC EARTHQUAKE
KW  - VEGETATION RECOVERY
