T2  - AUTOMATED PEOPLE MOVERS VI: CREATIVE ACCESS FOR MAJOR ACTIVITY CENTERS
LA  - English
CP  - 6th International Conference on Automated People Movers
AB  - This document reviews selected Issues which currently impact the urban transport activity from Caracas to Tokyo. It suggests the merit for use of a new transit technology - Aeromovel. While no one technology provides all answers to all mobility needs, Aeromovel has qualities which many communities are seeking. With the existence of two operating routes, one in Brasil and one in Indonesia, and the active design and planning for additional Aeromovel locations; transport leaders should have a growing interest in this pneumatic transit option for the near term.
   Aeromovel is an option with potential to reduce capital funding costs, raise service quality, and permit rapid installation when demand capacities are below 9,000 persons per direction pet hour. Within this demand level, the Aeromovel Technology is termed as 'Aeromidi'.
